Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteSecondaryPGNet(25.10)                        deleteSecondaryPGNet(25.10)

Name
       deleteSecondaryPGNet  -  Deletes  Power/Ground  (P/G) net wire segments
       from specified instances

Syntax
       deleteSecondaryPGNet

       [-help]

       -insts <inst>+

       -net <net>

       Deletes Power/Ground (P/G) net wire segments from specified  instances.
       This  command  provides an easy way to delete the routing from specific
       instance P/G pins to stripes.

       Note: This command does not support dangling secondary P/G nets.

Parameters
       -help  Prints the usage of the command. For a detailed  description  of
              the command, use the man command:

              man deleteSecondaryPGNet

       -insts <inst>+
              Specifies  the  list  of instances that have a secondary PG pin.
              Wildcards are supported in instance names.

              If one or more specified instances does  not  connect  with  the
              specified net, the tool displays a warning and ignores those in-
              stances.

       -net <net_name>
              Specifies the net name.

              Note: <net_name> does not take any wildcard values.

Examples
              *

                The  following command deletes the routing from the instance A
                P/G pin in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                deleteSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A}

              *

                The following command deletes the routing from the P/G pins in
                instances A and B in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                deleteSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A B}

              *

                The following command deletes the routing from the P/G pins in
                instances A/B1 and A/B2 in net VDD_1 to the power stripe:

                deleteSecondaryPGNet -net VDD_1 -insts {A/*}

